ACPI: scope CIX SCMI _STA override to old-firmware SCMI children

CIX's compatibility quirk force-enables old-firmware SCMI protocol child
devices with _STA=0, but the HID/UID match alone is broader than the
commented intent. Only apply the quirk to CIXHA008/CIXHA009 devices below the
CIXHA006 SCMI controller so similarly named devices elsewhere cannot be
unhidden accidentally.

Also leave devices alone when firmware already reports a nonzero _STA so the
compatibility shim self-disables on fixed firmware.

---
diff --git a/drivers/acpi/sta_quirk.c b/drivers/acpi/sta_quirk.c
--- a/drivers/acpi/sta_quirk.c
+++ b/drivers/acpi/sta_quirk.c
@@ -25,12 +25,21 @@ static const struct acpi_device_id cix_scmi_proto_sta_ids[] = {
 bool acpi_sta_override_firmware_quirk(struct acpi_device *adev,
 				       unsigned long long *status)
 {
+	struct acpi_device *parent;
+
 	if (acpi_match_device_ids(adev, cix_scmi_proto_sta_ids))
 		return false;
 
+	parent = acpi_dev_parent(adev);
+	if (!parent || !acpi_dev_hid_uid_match(parent, "CIXHA006", NULL))
+		return false;
+
 	if (!acpi_dev_uid_match(adev, 0))
 		return false;
 
+	if (*status != 0)
+		return false;
+
 	*status = ACPI_STA_DEFAULT;
 	return true;
 }
